  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CRS Support to Small-Scale Food Production for Poor Families in Lal District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CRS will work with landless poor and female&#x2010;headed households to improve their food security and utilize their limited natural resources more effectively. This project will work with target beneficiaries to improve their access to more diverse crops at the household&#x2010;level, and improve their use of natural resources in the areas surrounding their homes for this purpose.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Groups of landless households are trained in keyhole garden technology and use, Landless households are trained in principles of vegetable planting and harvesting, Landless households are trained in methods of vegetable preparation for consumption, Target households are provided a variety of vegetable seed inputs by Quarter 1 of the project for use in keyhole gardens and plastic to maintain during winter, Trainings are conducted with target men and women about composting and waste-water usage, Natural resource mapping is done with men and women in the community, Target community members are guided to identify simple activities to aid keyhole gardens</narrative>
  </description>
